    • parseHQConfig

      public boolean parseHQConfig​(HQ hq, Config config)
      This method finds and parses the initial HQ setup and customization configuration file. Taking info such as: SITENAMES, Margins for sell and buy transactions and the current year.
      Returns:
      boolean true if successful.

    • parseProjectConfig

      public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Double> parseProjectConfig​(java.util.List<java.lang.String> listToBeParsed)
      This method takes the list of strings belonging to a ProjectConfigfile and parses them. This method uses the stream API to handle and assign the individual currencyNames and their assigned total amounts to be entered into the "moneyBox". The Strings are widely used in the application. Used to keep track of which currencies were available or used at specific periods.
      Parameters:
      listToBeParsed - the contents of a ProjectConfigFile.
      Returns:
      Map String, Double for use to keep track of which currencies are available.

    • parseCurrencyConfig

      public static java.util.List<affix.java.project.moneyservice.ExchangeRate> parseCurrencyConfig​(java.util.List<java.lang.String> listToBeParsed)
      This method takes the list of strings belonging to a CurrencyConfigfile and parses them. Parses currency Configuration files into the daily ExchangeRates which are later mapped with a localDate as Key.
      Parameters:
      listToBeParsed - the contents of a CurrencyConfigFile.
      Returns:
      List ExchangeRate for use by the system when running stats-calculations.

    • readReport

      public java.util.List<affix.java.project.moneyservice.Transaction> readReport​(java.lang.String filename)
      Reads a file filled with transactions. Parses the date and handled site.
      Parameters:
      filename - from which to read the objects (Handled as Path).
      Returns:
      List Transaction from the report, these are handled in HQ.runStatistics().
